com.flowpowered.commons.store.block.impl

Class AtomicVariableWidthArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.flowpowered.commons.store.block.impl.AtomicVariableWidthArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class AtomicVariableWidthArray
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This class implements a variable width Atomic array. It is backed by an AtomicInteger array.

    Entries widths can be a power of 2 from 1 to 32
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • AtomicVariableWidthArray

        public AtomicVariableWidthArray(int length,
                                int width)
        Creates a variable Atomic array. The width must be a power of two from 1 to 32 and the length must be a multiple of the number of elements that fit in an int after packing.
        Parameters:
        length - the length of the array
        width - the number of bits in each entry

      • AtomicVariableWidthArray

        public AtomicVariableWidthArray(int length,
                                int width,
                                int[] initial)
        Creates a variable Atomic array. The width must be a power of two from 1 to 32 and the length must be a multiple of the number of elements that fit in an int after packing.
        Parameters:
        length - the length of the array
        width - the number of bits in each entry
        initial - the initial state of the array (in packed format)
